Get Standard Names

Source: R/standards-helpers.R
get_standard_names.Rd

Returns a character vector of all recognized standard names.

Usage

get_standard_names()

Value

Character vector of canonical standard names.

See also

Other standards: auto_detect_standards(), get_recognized_standards(), get_standard_type(), is_standard(), match_standards(), normalize_standard_name()

Examples

get_standard_names()
#>  [1] "PS 1683"    "PS A"       "PS B"       "PS C"       "PS D"      
#>  [6] "PMMA A"     "PMMA B"     "PMMA C"     "PMMA D"     "PEG A"     
#> [11] "PEG B"      "PEG C"      "PEG D"      "Pullulan A" "Pullulan B"
#> [16] "Pullulan C" "Pullulan D" "Standard 1" "Standard 2" "Standard 3"
#> [21] "Standard 4"
